title: For Sale:  Beretta PX4 Storm Compact 9mm w Crossbreed Holster
postcontent:
Hello,

I have for sale a used, but good condition, Beretta PX4 Storm Compact 9mm.  It comes with the box and 2 15 round magazines.  Somehow I ended up with 2 of them and one needs to go.  

The firearm is very reliable.  I have had it out to the range on several occasions and I have put around 400 rounds through it with no issues. This scope is the one that had the Christmas tree ranging reticle pattern. The ranging reticle was designed so that the shooter could aim at different targets at multiple ranges without having to adjust the elevation on the scope. The reticle acquired its name because the reticle is shaped similarly to a Christmas tree. The reticle is used with the trunk serving as the center of the target while the branches of different widths and heights serve as range and windage markers. It is a 10 power scope and the scope's ranges are from 500 to 2000m. 

The scope comes complete with the rings that came from the Barrett factory. I believe these are the Barrett factory 30mm adjustable rings. title: For Sale/Trade:  Lee Enfield No.1 MKIII Ishapore
location: Rocky Mount, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Lee Enfield No. 1 MKIII ishapore scrub. Century Arms Import. Has a FR 44 which stands for field repair 1944 on the left side of the receiver. If you know about scrubs they were early British made rifles used by the Brits in India than later sold to the Indian Forces. After the war and the British lost power in India, the India Army scrubbed the British Markings from the receiver and barrels and put a screw in the stock to match the no.1 MKIII they were producing. 

This rifle has the screw, but it serves no purpose unlike the Indian rifles. All matching numbers besides the magazine. The serial number is pretty low for a mass produced war rifle. Metal is in good shape, besides minor pitting on the left side of receiver. This rifle still has Brit markings on the barrel. The bore has strong rifling. This rifle is a great shooter. 

Not really interested in trades unless it is a 17HMR, 22LR, or .22 MAG bolt action rifle. Can add cash for the right deal. Trade value $325 firm. Cash price is $325 obo.

Inside the Stoeger Model 2000 semi-auto shotgun is the Inertia Driven operating system, the heart of the world's most prestigious and reliable autoloaders.
